    <title ixia_locid="712">Managing Local Volume Groups Using the CLI</title>
    <shortdesc ixia_locid="713">You can use CLI commands to manage local volume groups.</shortdesc>
    <prolog>
        <author ixia_locid="714">Edward Knowlton</author>
    </prolog>
    <taskbody>
        <section id="section_N1001F_N1001C_N10001" ixia_locid="715">
            <p ixia_locid="17"><draft-comment author="jowens" ixia_locid="72">US65502 added
                    host-lvg-modify and associated parameter information; US68057 updated
                    host-lvg-modify syntax and related notes; US69978 updated host-lvg-modify syntax
                    ; CGTS-2902(-related) added concurrent-ops parm; US74975 add instance_backing
                    type "remote"</draft-comment>The following CLI commands are availabe for
                managing local volume groups:</p>
            <codeblock ixia_locid="26"><systemoutput ixia_locid="27">~(keystone_admin)$ </systemoutput><userinput ixia_locid="28">system host-lvg-list <varname ixia_locid="29">hostname</varname></userinput></codeblock>
            <codeblock ixia_locid="48"><systemoutput ixia_locid="49">~(keystone_admin)$ </systemoutput><userinput ixia_locid="50">system host-lvg-show <varname ixia_locid="51">hostname</varname> <varname ixia_locid="690">groupname</varname></userinput></codeblock>
            <codeblock ixia_locid="18"><systemoutput ixia_locid="19">~(keystone_admin)$ </systemoutput><userinput ixia_locid="20">system host-lvg-add <varname ixia_locid="21">hostname</varname> <varname ixia_locid="691">groupname</varname></userinput></codeblock>
            <codeblock ixia_locid="22"><systemoutput ixia_locid="23">~(keystone_admin)$ </systemoutput><userinput ixia_locid="24">system host-lvg-delete <varname ixia_locid="25">hostname</varname> <varname ixia_locid="83">groupname</varname></userinput></codeblock>
            <codeblock ixia_locid="52"><systemoutput ixia_locid="53">~(keystone_admin)$ </systemoutput><userinput ixia_locid="54">system host-lvg-modify [-b <varname ixia_locid="84">instance_backing</varname>] \
[-c <varname ixia_locid="701">concurrent_disk_operations</varname>] [-s <varname ixia_locid="57">size</varname>] <varname ixia_locid="55">hostname</varname> <varname ixia_locid="85">groupname</varname></userinput></codeblock>
            <p ixia_locid="58">Where:<dl>
                    <dlentry ixia_locid="702">
                        <dt ixia_locid="703"><varname ixia_locid="704">instance_backing</varname></dt>
                        <dd ixia_locid="705">
                            <p ixia_locid="706">is the storage method for the local volume group
                                    (<option ixia_locid="91">lvm</option>, <option ixia_locid="92">image</option>, or <option ixia_locid="716">remote</option>)</p>
                        </dd>
                    </dlentry>
                    <dlentry ixia_locid="707">
                        <dt ixia_locid="708"><varname ixia_locid="709">concurrent_disk_operations</varname></dt>
                        <dd ixia_locid="710">
                            <p ixia_locid="711">is the number of I/O intensive disk operations, such
                                as glance image downloads or image format conversions, that can
                                occur at the same time</p>
                        </dd>
                    </dlentry>
                    <dlentry ixia_locid="64">
                        <dt ixia_locid="65"><varname ixia_locid="66">size</varname></dt>
                        <dd ixia_locid="67">
                            <p ixia_locid="68"> is the space in MB to allot for instances logical
                                volume space (specified only if the storage method is <option ixia_locid="689">lvm</option>) </p>
                        </dd>
                    </dlentry>
                    <dlentry ixia_locid="93">
                        <dt ixia_locid="94"><varname ixia_locid="95">hostname</varname></dt>
                        <dd ixia_locid="96">
                            <p ixia_locid="97">is the name of the host</p>
                        </dd>
                    </dlentry>
                </dl><dl>
                    <dlentry ixia_locid="59">
                        <dt ixia_locid="60"><varname ixia_locid="61">groupname</varname></dt>
                        <dd ixia_locid="62">
                            <p ixia_locid="63"> is the name of the local volume group</p>
                            <note id="note_N1012C_N10123_N10117_N10114_N100A2_N1001F_N1001C_N10001" ixia_locid="38">
                                <p ixia_locid="39">The only valid <nameliteral ixia_locid="40">groupname</nameliteral> is <nameliteral ixia_locid="41">nova-local</nameliteral>. This parameter is <i ixia_locid="79">not</i> required for <cmdname ixia_locid="80">system host-lvg-modify</cmdname>.</p>
                            </note>
                        </dd>
                    </dlentry>
                </dl></p>
        </section>
    </taskbody>
